{
  "info": {
    "name": "Card Transaction System",
    "description": "## Pré-requisitos\n\n**Local:**\n```\ndocker-compose up -d\nSPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=local-rich ./mvnw spring-boot:run\n```\nSelecione o environment **local-rich**.\n\n**AWS:** preencha `baseUrl` no environment **aws** com a Function URL do Lambda.\n\n---\n\n## Fluxo\n1. Execute **Auth / Login** → `token` é salvo automaticamente no environment\n2. Execute os pares `Xa → Xb` de cada cenário\n3. O `correlationId` é propagado automaticamente entre as requests do mesmo cenário",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "exec": ["// Collection-level pre-request: nenhum"],
        "type": "text/javascript"
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "Login e obtenção do JWT. O token é salvo automaticamente no environment.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Token presente', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.environment.set('token', json.token);",
                  "console.log('Token salvo no environment.');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"username\": \"{{username}}\",\n    \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login",
            "description": "Credenciais vêm do environment (`username` / `password`).\nO campo `token` é populado automaticamente no environment após o login."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Cenário 1 — Caminho Feliz",
      "description": "**Cartão:** VISA `4111 1111 1111 1111`  \n**Perfil:** limite R$ 10.000 · usado R$ 0 · max 12x · taxa 1,99%/mês  \n**Request:** R$ 500 / 3x  \n**Resultado esperado:** `APPROVED`",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1a. POST /process",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Garante token antes de chamar",
                  "if (!pm.environment.get('token')) {",
                  "    console.warn('token vazio — execute Auth/Login primeiro');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 202 Accepted', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('correlationId presente', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.correlationId).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('transactionId presente', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.transactionId).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.environment.set('correlationId_happy', json.correlationId);",
                  "console.log('correlationId salvo:', json.correlationId);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"transactionId\": \"txn-happy-001\",\n    \"uuidTransaction\": \"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001\",\n    \"cardDataRequest\": {\n        \"number\": \"4111111111111111\",\n        \"cvv\": \"123\",\n        \"brand\": \"VISA\",\n        \"name\": \"JOAO DA SILVA\"\n    },\n    \"amount\": 500.00,\n    \"installments\": 3,\n    \"callbackUrl\": \"{{webhookUrl}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/process"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "1b. GET /status → APPROVED",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "console.log('status:', json.status, '| reason:', json.reason);",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Status válido', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.be.oneOf(['PENDING', 'APPROVED', 'REJECTED']);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (json.status !== 'PENDING') {",
                  "    pm.test('Resultado esperado: APPROVED', () => {",
                  "        pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('APPROVED');",
                  "    });",
                  "} else {",
                  "    console.warn('Ainda PENDING — aguarde a saga e reenvie.');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/status/{{correlationId_happy}}",
            "description": "Execute após `1a`. Se retornar PENDING, aguarde alguns segundos e reenvie."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Cenário 2 — Transação Negada",
      "description": "**Cartão:** MASTER `5500 0055 5555 5559`  \n**Perfil:** limite R$ 500 · usado R$ 490 · disponível R$ 10  \n**Request:** R$ 200 / 1x (total com juros R$ 203,98 > R$ 10,00)  \n**Resultado esperado:** `REJECTED` (regra de negócio — crédito insuficiente)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "2a. POST /process",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 202 Accepted', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('correlationId presente', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.correlationId).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.environment.set('correlationId_denied', json.correlationId);",
                  "console.log('correlationId salvo:', json.correlationId);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"transactionId\": \"txn-denied-001\",\n    \"uuidTransaction\": \"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002\",\n    \"cardDataRequest\": {\n        \"number\": \"5500005555555559\",\n        \"cvv\": \"321\",\n        \"brand\": \"MASTER\",\n        \"name\": \"MARIA SOUZA\"\n    },\n    \"amount\": 200.00,\n    \"installments\": 1,\n    \"callbackUrl\": \"{{webhookUrl}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/process"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2b. GET /status → REJECTED (crédito)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "console.log('status:', json.status, '| reason:', json.reason);",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Status válido', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.be.oneOf(['PENDING', 'APPROVED', 'REJECTED']);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (json.status !== 'PENDING') {",
                  "    pm.test('Resultado esperado: REJECTED', () => {",
                  "        pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('REJECTED');",
                  "    });",
                  "    pm.test('Reason menciona crédito', () => {",
                  "        pm.expect(json.reason).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "    });",
                  "} else {",
                  "    console.warn('Ainda PENDING — aguarde a saga e reenvie.');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/status/{{correlationId_denied}}"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Cenário 3 — Bloqueada por Fraude",
      "description": "**Cartão:** VISA `4000 0000 0000 0002`  \n**Perfil:** limite R$ 10.000 · usado R$ 0 (crédito OK)  \n**Cache Redis:** `FRAUD:acd08f29-a41f-2e55-ab0c-4f774b1562b0 = {\"score\":95}` (seed automático)  \n**Resultado esperado:** `REJECTED` imediato no orquestrador (score 95 ≥ threshold 80)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "3a. POST /process",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 202 Accepted', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('correlationId presente', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.correlationId).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.environment.set('correlationId_fraud', json.correlationId);",
                  "console.log('correlationId salvo:', json.correlationId);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"transactionId\": \"txn-fraud-001\",\n    \"uuidTransaction\": \"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003\",\n    \"cardDataRequest\": {\n        \"number\": \"4000000000000002\",\n        \"cvv\": \"999\",\n        \"brand\": \"VISA\",\n        \"name\": \"CARLOS FRAUDE\"\n    },\n    \"amount\": 100.00,\n    \"installments\": 1,\n    \"callbackUrl\": \"{{webhookUrl}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/process"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "3b. GET /status → REJECTED (fraude)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "console.log('status:', json.status, '| reason:', json.reason);",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Status válido', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.be.oneOf(['PENDING', 'APPROVED', 'REJECTED']);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (json.status !== 'PENDING') {",
                  "    pm.test('Resultado esperado: REJECTED', () => {",
                  "        pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('REJECTED');",
                  "    });",
                  "    pm.test('Reason menciona fraud score', () => {",
                  "        pm.expect(json.reason).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/status/{{correlationId_fraud}}",
            "description": "Para este cenário, como a rejeição ocorre no orquestrador (antes da saga), o status já deve ser REJECTED imediatamente."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Utilitários",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /status por ID manual",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/status/:correlationId",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["status", ":correlationId"],
              "variable": [
                {
                  "key": "correlationId",
                  "value": "",
                  "description": "Cole o correlationId aqui"
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /process — idempotência (reenvio txn-happy-001)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 202', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "const original = pm.environment.get('correlationId_happy');",
                  "",
                  "if (original) {",
                  "    pm.test('Mesmo correlationId (idempotente)', () => {",
                  "        pm.expect(json.correlationId).to.eql(original);",
                  "    });",
                  "} else {",
                  "    console.warn('Execute o Cenário 1 antes para comparar.');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"transactionId\": \"txn-happy-001\",\n    \"uuidTransaction\": \"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001\",\n    \"cardDataRequest\": {\n        \"number\": \"4111111111111111\",\n        \"cvv\": \"123\",\n        \"brand\": \"VISA\",\n        \"name\": \"JOAO DA SILVA\"\n    },\n    \"amount\": 500.00,\n    \"installments\": 3,\n    \"callbackUrl\": null\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/process",
            "description": "Reenvia a mesma `transactionId` do Cenário 1. Deve retornar o mesmo `correlationId` sem criar nova transação."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /process — validação (body inválido)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 400 Bad Request', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Erro de validação', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.error).to.eql('Validation Failed');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Fields preenchidos', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.fields).to.be.an('array').and.not.empty;",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"transactionId\": \"\",\n    \"amount\": -1,\n    \"installments\": 99\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/process",
            "description": "Payload propositalmente inválido para testar o GlobalExceptionHandler → 400."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
